ENTRY            A0661   20260207   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0661001   20260207   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 15         49
TITLE      The measurement of isotopic cross sections of 12C beam
           fragmentation on liquid hydrogen at 3.66 GeV/nucleon
AUTHOR     (A.Korejwo, T.Dzikowski, M.Giller, J.Wdowczyk,
           V.V.Perelygin, A.V.Zarubin)
INSTITUTE  (3POLLOU,4ZZZDUB)
REFERENCE  (J,JP/G,26,1171,2000)
FACILITY   (SYNCY,4ZZZDUB) Slow extraction beam VP-1
MONITOR    (1-H-1(6-C-12,INL)1-H-1,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (,B.M.Bobchenko+,J,YF,30,1553,1979) The value of the
           inelastic cross section of the 12C + p reaction was
           taken as 250 +/- 2 mb.
COMMENT    -By authors. In this case all the nuclei produced by
           beam fragmentation are emitted in a narrow cone along
           the beam direction and their momenta per nucleon are
           close to the projectile value. Therefore, it is
           possible to detect all the nuclei that are produced,
           including those with very small energy in the
           projectile reference frame.
DETECTOR   (SPEC) The ANOMALON magnetic spectrometer is based on
           a system of multiwire proportional chambers (MWPC)
           and an analysing magnet. It also includes a Cherenkov
           hodoscope for determining fragment charges, a trigger
           system consisting of scintillation and Cherenkov
           detectors, and a beam monitor. For the beam
           fragmentation cross section measurements the ANOMALON
           set-up was equipped with a liquid hydrogen target.
           MWPCs constitute a coordinate detector for
           determining. The positions of the charged-particle
           tracks. More detailed description see:
REL-REF    (M,,Yu.T.Borzunov+,J,KSO,,(1/81),1,1997) and
           A.V.Zarubin et al., JINR B1-1-93-444 (1993)
SAMPLE     The target is 59 mm in diameter and 136 mm long
            (equivalent to 0.94 g/cm2). The total thickness of
           the two Mylar windows is 67 mg/cm2.
METHOD     (SITA,EXTB,COINC)
CORRECTION The background correction factor has been calculated
           separately for each isotope using the results of
           measurements with an empty target and with hydrogen.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical error.
           (ERR-1) The systematic errors are due mainly to
           uncertainty regarding the efficiency of track
           reconstruction (varying with Z). Other factors being
           negligible.
           (ERR-T) Total uncertainty.
HISTORY    (20040212C)
           (20040212U) Last checking has been done.
           (20260207A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           Energy value updated according to presentation in the
           article. REL-REF -> MONIT-REF. MONITOR added.
ENDBIB              49
COMMON               3          3
EN         MONIT      MONIT-ERR
GEV/A      MB         MB
      3.66       250.         2.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           56
SUBENT        A0661002   20260207   20260401   20260401       A131
